The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Nagaon, June 16: Suspected militants of the Dima Halam Daogah (Jewel Gorlosa) outfit today gunned down 12 Zeme Nagas in Assams North Cachar Hills district in the single largest massacre since ethnic conflict broke out there in March. Seven of those killed were children.           
	The militants also set fire to 62 houses in a village. The Dimasa tribals of Assam, who have been demanding a Dimaraji state, have allegedly been targeting the Zeme Nagas to ensure domination in the district.                   
	 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): Islamic seminary Darul Uloom Deoband has said Muslims should eat the meat of only those animals that are slaughtered by community members after reading the Bismillah. The fatwa was issued on a query whether Muslims could eat meat from a factory.                   
	 Ranchi/Giridih: Naxalites on Tuesday killed four policemen in a Palamau village near the Bihar-Jharkhand border. The police team was ambushed when it was patrolling in the area. Six policemen were injured in the three-hour encounter.                  
	 Madurai (PTI): A bomb packed in a tiffin box exploded near a flyover on the outskirts of the city on Monday night, injuring one person. A combing operation by police after the explosion led to the recovery of 10 similar devices in the area.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): Bombay High Court on Tuesday set aside the bail granted to MNS chief Raj Thackeray by a lower court and asked him to surrender before the railway court in Kalyan on June 29. The case involves the attack by his party workers on candidates appearing for a railway examination in October 2008.                  
	 Agra (PTI): An illegal factory that allegedly used animal bones to make adulterated ghee has been discovered by district authorities. The workers had fled when the team raided the unit. The district magistrate has ordered a probe.                                                                                                                           
